  <title>GLib.ascii_strdown</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function ascii_strdown(str: String, len: Number(gssize)): String {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_ascii_strdown()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Converts all upper case ASCII letters to lower case ASCII letters.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>str</code></title>
  <p>a string</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>len</code></title>
  <p>length of <code>str</code> in bytes, or -1 if <code>str</code> is nul-terminated</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>a newly-allocated string, with all the upper case
    characters in <code>str</code> converted to lower case, with semantics that
    exactly match <link xref="GLib.ascii_tolower"/>. (Note that this is unlike the
    old <link xref="GLib.strdown"/>, which modified the string in place.)</p>
</item>
</terms>

